Experts expect, that from next year more than 80 percent of young parents let their babies vaccinate against pneumococci.
The pneumococal vaccine is also a big change because as the first vaccination in children is covered by health companies, not by the state.
Insurance companies should spend more money on prophylaxis, to save on treatment later, explains Cabrnochová.
The doctors will have to buy the vaccines themselves.
However, pediatricians are concerned about the purchase of vaccines.
Previously, vaccines had to be bought by insurance companies and distributed to doctors, just as when the state gives them other vaccines.
Some Members were afraid, however, that insurance companies could "take out the money from health insurance".
Doctors will have to buy the vaccines and wait until they are paid for by insurance companies.
It is estimated that pediatricians will invest in vaccines 40,000 a month, which is a remarkable sum.
It won't be easy, says Cabrnochova.
