New Silicon Valley
For many years, it was considered a secret city, inaccessible to Western visitors.
Selenograd, one of Moscow's ten districts, was in the Soviet Union a heavily guarded site for secret arms investigation.
Today, the community of 216,000 inhabitants, located 37 kilometers from the center of Moscow, is considered the "Russian Silicon Valley".
Important research and production centers for micro and nanoelectronics are located here.
Since September 2008, representatives of Selenograd have contacted the Riedberg Science Centre in Frankfurt, university institutes and companies at the Frankfurt Innovation Centre (FIZ).
Various mutual visits took place and now, on Wednesday, Selenograd and Riedberg sign in Frankfurt a "close collaboration protocol".
