Scientific exchange
This is a continuous scientific exchange.
But it also addresses trade relations.
The FIZ companies will have the opportunity to set foot in the growing Russian market.
In return, Russian scientific companies wish to have access to contracts in Germany.
Selenograd is the headquarters of major Russian companies and research institutes.
These include, for example, the Moscow Institute of Electronic Technology, the major Sitronics and Rossijskaja Elektronika consortia.
The community was founded in 1958 as the so-called "Socialist City of Planning" for weapons research.
