The Stuttgart 21 dimension is not high enough at all.
For the supporters of the project, it is simply "the new heart of Europe".
The law so. S21 is much more than the reduction of a railway station, rather than a monstrous construction project, which will precipitate to the capital of the Banden-Württemberga region a decade of chaos of irremediable construction sites.
Stuttgart 21 emerged from the spirit of the 1980s.
Terminals with rails, which end in the middle of the city, were considered at that time fossils of engineering of the nineteenth century, which acted as brakes of a modern railway traffic, since formerly a huge amount of time was needed to hook the locomotives from the back forward.
Roll, stop dry continue the journey; but so it must be done.
And that's why the terminals had to disappear: in Frankfurt and Munich.
And in Stuttgart: a station of passage, which is approximately half the way of the trans-European operating lines between Paris and Budapest/Bratislava; hence the slogan of "Heart of Europe".
The S21 will really be initiated, even though the visions of the 1980s are no longer compatible with reality.
Even the most ambitious designers have known that in the Hessian and Bavarian capitals it is almost unpayable to implement the reduction.
Railway terminals of course also do not have more entry and exit problems, since there are reversible locomotives with tractor unit and driver's carriage at both ends.
However: Stuttgart 21 including the new section built ICE towards Ulm will already be started.
Federal and communal politicians have so arranged.
The railway continues, also because the risks of the great individual infrastructure projects of the Republic are borne by the taxpayer and not by the State.
