One of the most important is the extension of more than 180 kilometers of long rails across the Rhine valley.
Since 1987 the route has been built at a slow pace.
It would be urgent here to step on the accelerator properly.
However, the S21 acts as a brake.
The section of the Rhine Valley will be the bottleneck for international freight transport: through the heart of Europe.
