Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and settled in Spain in 1979.
According to sources of the company, 62% of its business is generated in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. They work with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 workshops, 3,000 of them in Spain.
The global turnover of the Solera group (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will reach 557 million dollars, 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country the company will earn 19.1 million euros, 7.2% more than the previous year.
In 2005, the Solera group was worth $1 billion on the Stock Exchange, and now its shares are listed for a total value of $2.4 billion.
Since 2007 it has been listed on the New York Stock Exchange and is included in the Standard & Poor's reference index.
Internet Auction of Accidentated Cars
Last October the Solera group bought Autoonline, an online platform for the sale of cars such as motorcycles or sinister special vehicles.
The operation involved a disbursement of 59.5 million euros for 85% of the company's capital, which could be extended next year to the remaining 15%.
The objective of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of accessing an immense international market.
This valuation and sales service is exclusively aimed at professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, renters, workshops, scrapyards and professional sellers who must register before starting operations.
This platform was established in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, 500,000 of them in Germany.
Among its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The website currently has more than 1,500 registered vendors and 4,000 experts.
3,000 advertisements are managed daily and about 100 new advertisements are included in the Spanish market each day.
According to Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been decommissioned cannot be recirculated, but certain parts that are not damaged can be used as a spare.
Cars with historical value can be discharged even if they have been decommissioned after a long time.
Workshop budget in four steps
With the Auda-Worker tool, the Audatex company guarantees that the user gets a budget in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search for the replacement, create budget and generate budget.
Ease of use is an essential conditioning factor for these systems, especially to convince older professionals, who to a greater or lesser extent tend to be more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 passenger cars, 109 SUVs, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, a computer with an internet connection is required to use it.
Once the model to be repaired is identified using its frame number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as labor price, surcharges or discounts, and then can print the quote to deliver to the customer.
AudaWorker is not an evaluation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a catalog of references.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop orientation does not include estimated labor times.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which the customer can finance.
Audatex is currently working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with very good eyes, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it over to see the inner face.
